'''Gustavo Sannia''' (Napoli, 13 May 1875 – 21 December 1930) was an Italian mathematician working in [[differential geometry]], [[projective geometry]], and [[summation of series]]. He was the son of [[Achille Sannia]], mathematician and senator of the [[Kingdom of Italy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://matematica.unibocconi.it/autore/gustavo-sannia|title=Gustavo Sannia|publisher=[[Bocconi University]]|language=it}}</ref>

