[[File:Rusins Freivalds (2009) front.jpg|thumb|Freivalds in June 2009.]]
'''Rūsiņš Mārtiņš Freivalds''' (10 November 1942 &ndash; 4 January 2016) was a [[Latvia]]n [[computer scientist]] and mathematician. He was a member of [[Latvian Academy of Sciences]] from 1992. He discovered [[Freivalds' algorithm]] for checking the correctness of matrix products. He also taught at the [[University of Latvia]] with students including [[Daina Taimina]] and [[Andris Ambainis]]. He was born in [[Cesvaine]] and studied at [[Moscow State University]] (MSU).
Freivalds died from a [[heart attack]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.computationalcomplexity.org/2016/01/rusins-freivalds-1942-2016.html|title=Rūsiņš Freivalds (1942-2016)|work=Computational Complexity|date=6 January 2016|accessdate=11 January 2016|author=[[Lance Fortnow|Fortnow, Lance]]}}</ref> on 4 January 2016 in [[Riga]], aged 73.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.delfi.lv/news/national/politics/muziba-aizgajis-profesors-rusins-martins-freivalds.d?id=46907459|title=Mūžībā aizgājis profesors Rūsiņš Mārtiņš Freivalds|work=delfi.lv|language=Latvian|date=4 January 2016|accessdate=11 January 2016}}</ref>
